Cell[TextData[{
 "Well, I didn\[CloseCurlyQuote]t have to wait long to get a unique answer to \
my question. The final solution to this problem tends to resemble a plane in \
space as a direct result the leading term in the sum because we defined the \
plane as an initial condition at the start of the problem. It\
\[CloseCurlyQuote]s worth noting however that this solution is ",
 StyleBox["not",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " a perfect plane since there\[CloseCurlyQuote]s a small indentation in the \
center of our final result. If anything, this solution reminds me of the \
graphs shown when large objects bend space time and create indentations. This \
behavior is most frequently associated with black holes since these massive \
objects tend to create giant pits that can be graphed out using advanced \
software. I\[CloseCurlyQuote]m babbling now so let\[CloseCurlyQuote]s move \
onto the second part of the assignment. "
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.858092400133841*^9, 
  3.858092736841905*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"0def502b-5abd-4813-a111-\
5b3336790d06"]
}, Open  ]]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["\<\
3.) Refer back to your thoughts on HW6 about the Heat equation solutions and \
compare the solutions to your expectations. \
\>", "Chapter",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.858005817578817*^9, 
  3.8580058499283533`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"6cb1b341-0132-4e55-baae-\
41a553a1bfef"],

Cell["\<\
In the previous homework assignment, I found some rather disappointing \
solutions to the heat equation in the form of a plane and several sinusoidal \
variations. In this assignment, I found more of the same since these \
solutions tell a similar story, just in higher dimensions. This runs contrary \
from our predictions since we previously expected radically different \
solutions as a result of the higher dimensions. I guess we can\
\[CloseCurlyQuote]t really complain since our solutions all use the principle \
of separation of variables and we get results to match. \
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.858023281288044*^9, 3.858023371702374*^9}, {
  3.858023572090293*^9, 3.85802362374876*^9}, {3.858023720910513*^9, 
  3.8580237216050034`*^9}, {3.8580237753055897`*^9, 3.858023821748086*^9}, {
  3.858023871638916*^9, 3.858023907740876*^9}, {3.858023943237997*^9, 
  3.858023997376096*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"269deca0-ae09-48d2-b094-\
2fbf3fa6d145"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell["3.8 Problems", "Subtitle",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.858005026614399*^9, 
  3.858005029101242*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"52598d9e-9f85-441d-adb3-\
086ab488a484"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[TextData[{
 "Plot all solutions to Laplace\[CloseCurlyQuote]s Equation: ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     SubscriptBox["u", "xx"], "+", 
     SubscriptBox["u", "yy"]}], "=", "0"}], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->"TraditionalForm",ExpressionUUID->
  "1cffdc07-b268-47b8-8ff6-38d8e007ad65"],
 ". Evaluate the solutions and their behaviors. Discuss characteristics and \
similarities. Compare with previous solutions to the heat and wave \
equations."
}], "Chapter",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8580051539833403`*^9, 
  3.858005227089869*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"524e6217-82a4-4675-9f11-\
e98e51d086d7"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[TextData[{
 "a.) a = b = \[Pi], ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     SubscriptBox["f", "2"], "(", "x", ")"}], " ", "=", " ", "x"}], 
   TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->"TraditionalForm",ExpressionUUID->
  "89db083d-7449-4b8a-9075-6de0fbf1c1b1"],
 ", and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     SubscriptBox["f", "1"], "(", "x", ")"}], " ", "=", " ", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{
      SubscriptBox["g", "1"], "(", "y", ")"}], " ", "=", " ", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{
       SubscriptBox["g", "2"], "(", "y", ")"}], " ", "=", " ", "0"}]}]}], 
   TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->"TraditionalForm",ExpressionUUID->
  "63f7fcf1-ab97-45eb-8390-8af24b8e0fe2"],
 "."
}], "Section",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.858005428843525*^9, 3.8580055083930273`*^9}, 
   3.858005686811532*^9, {3.858007150549878*^9, 
   3.858007158042616*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"15a8a1ac-658c-4646-b7d2-\
b9841a4b8e68"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "u(x,y) = ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    UnderoverscriptBox["\[Sum]", 
     RowBox[{"n", "=", "1"}], "\[Infinity]"], 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"sin", "(", "nx", ")"}], "*", 
     FractionBox[
      RowBox[{"[", 
       RowBox[{
        RowBox[{"-", "2"}], 
        SuperscriptBox[
         RowBox[{"(", 
          RowBox[{"-", "1"}], ")"}], "n"]}], "]"}], 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"sinh", "(", "n\[Pi]", ")"}], "*", "n"}]], 
     RowBox[{"sinh", "(", "ny", ")"}]}]}], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->"TraditionalForm",ExpressionUUID->
  "78ace24f-9489-4e69-945f-4ee3bf8a3e47"],
 ". Lets just evaluate one term from this series for brevity.\n\[Rule]u(x,y) \
= sin(x)*sinh(y)"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.858007162101696*^9, 3.858007339347426*^9}, {
  3.858007556270961*^9, 
  3.8580075672267237`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"7c4f0f68-af32-4611-bca2-\
1cec5cf7cd91"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"Mariah", " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     SubscriptBox["u", "4"], "[", 
     RowBox[{"x_", ",", "y_"}], "]"}], "=", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"Sin", "[", "x", "]"}], "*", 
     RowBox[{"Sinh", "[", "y", "]"}]}]}]}], ";"}]], "Input",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.858007357308814*^9, 3.858007423403666*^9}},
 CellLabel->"In[19]:=",ExpressionUUID->"163bba78-c832-4f2d-86d2-f9e784184e2e"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"Plot3D", "[", 
  RowBox[{"Mariah", ",", 
   RowBox[{"{", 
